President Donald J. Trump has announced his intent to nominate several individuals to key positions in his administration. These nominations include James Thomas Abbott of Virginia to be a Member of the Federal Labor Relations Authority, Larry Edward Andre Jr. of Texas to be Ambassador to the Republic of Djibouti, Robert Behler of Pennsylvania to be Director of Operational Test and Evaluation at the Department of Defense, and James Bridenstine of Oklahoma to be Administrator of NASA. Other nominations include Thomas L. Carter of South Carolina to be the Representative of the United States on the Council of the International Civil Aviation Organization, John C. Demers of Virginia to be an Assistant Attorney General at the Department of Justice, and Nina Maria Fite of Pennsylvania to be Ambassador to the Republic of Angola.